OL,3,C'Pressure release valve': The new law
OL,4,Cguaranteeing leave for unpaid carers
OL,6,FFor example, an employee can take
OL,7,Fthree days of leave as long as they
OL,8,Fgive at least six days of notice.
OL,10,FThe leave can be used to take care of
OL,11,Fsomeone who has a disability, needs
OL,12,Fcare because of old age, or has a long
OL,13,Fterm illness of more than three months.
OL,15,FIt is a day one right - meaning
OL,16,Femployees are entitled to the leave as
OL,17,Fsoon as they start work.
